---
const pageTitle = "Claims AI Reliability Platform";
const pageDescription =
  "A governed release and monitoring system for deciding when a claims knowledge assistant is safe enough to scale — and when it should be restricted, reviewed, or rolled back.";

const heroMetrics = [
  { label: "Release candidates evaluated", value: "3" },
  { label: "Real bug caught before release", value: "1" },
  { label: "Blockers in approved RC", value: "0" },
  { label: "Live rollback recommendation", value: "Yes" },
];

const whyPrototypeWasNotEnough = [
  "A fluent answer is not the same as a safe answer",
  "Claims workflows have boundary cases where escalation matters more than helpfulness",
  "Management needed release evidence before broader adoption, not confidence based on a good demo",
  "Even an approved release still needed monitoring in case live behavior later degraded",
];

const platformLayers = [
  {
    title: "Governed assistant",
    text: "A FastAPI claims knowledge assistant built with release-aware behavior, explicit retrieval control, and boundary-sensitive answer logic rather than open-ended assistant behavior.",
  },
  {
    title: "Benchmark release gate",
    text: "A structured evaluation layer across smoke, release-gate, boundary, and change-sensitive benchmark suites, with blocker logic, scoring, and release recommendation.",
  },
  {
    title: "Live monitoring and incident logic",
    text: "A telemetry and monitoring layer that converts unsafe live interactions into incidents, review queue items, and containment recommendations instead of leaving risk hidden inside logs.",
  },
  {
    title: "Packaged runtime with persistence",
    text: "A Docker and PostgreSQL-backed runtime that persists telemetry and monitoring state so the system feels operational, not just locally demoable.",
  },
];

const bugStoryBullets = [
  "A legal-liability / out-of-scope boundary case entered a product-line boundary branch first",
  "The answer was blocked, but it did not behave like a true mandatory escalation path",
  "That meant the system was technically restrictive, but operationally weaker than it should have been",
  "The benchmark exposed that behavior, the service logic was fixed, and the release decision improved because of it",
];

const liveMonitoringBullets = [
  "A deliberately unsafe post-release interaction was injected into the live workflow",
  "The assistant answered directly where escalation should have happened",
  "That event triggered multiple incidents across boundary, escalation, and grounding-related logic",
  "The platform also created a P1 review queue item and raised release degradation incidents",
  "The top containment action became rollback_release",
];

const runtimeBullets = [
  "Docker and Docker Compose packaged the assistant, control room, and PostgreSQL-backed persistence into one runnable environment",
  "PostgreSQL was used where it added real value: telemetry storage, monitoring storage, and operational state persistence",
  "The governed retrieval path was deliberately kept intact rather than rewritten just to force infrastructure into the answer path",
  "That was a disciplined choice: the retrieval behavior was already explicit, benchmarked, and central to release-gate behavior",
];

const imageAssets = {
  heroLoop: "/images/projects/claims-ai-reliability/claims-reliability-hero-loop.png",
  releaseProgression: "/images/projects/claims-ai-reliability/claims-reliability-release-progression.png",
  bugFlow: "/images/projects/claims-ai-reliability/claims-reliability-bug-fix-flow.png",
  controlRoomCritical: "/images/projects/claims-ai-reliability/claims-reliability-control-room-critical.png",
  incidentsReviewQueue: "/images/projects/claims-ai-reliability/claims-reliability-incidents-review-queue.png",
  dockerRuntime: "/images/projects/claims-ai-reliability/claims-reliability-docker-runtime.png",
};

const finalSignals = [
  "This project is stronger than a normal GenAI case because it proves release discipline, operational monitoring, and rollback readiness rather than just answer generation.",
  "It shows that I can work on the harder problem behind enterprise AI adoption: not only whether a system can answer, but whether the business can trust, govern, and contain it.",
];
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="description" content={pageDescription} />
    <title>{pageTitle} | Antonio González Martín</title>

    <style>
      :root {
        --bg: #04101c;
        --bg-2: #071726;
        --bg-3: #0a1c2d;

        --text: #f4f7fb;
        --soft: #d8e3f0;
        --muted: #9eb1c6;

        --accent-cyan: #7dd3fc;
        --accent-blue: #60a5fa;
        --accent-indigo: #818cf8;
        --accent-red: #f87171;
        --accent-amber: #fbbf24;
        --accent-green: #4ade80;

        --line: rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.16);
        --line-strong: rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.28);

        --panel: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035);
        --panel-strong: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);

        --shadow-soft: 0 18px 50px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.26);
        --shadow-lift: 0 24px 70px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.34);
        --max: 1180px;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      html {
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--text);
        font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.7;
        background:
          radial-gradient(circle at 12% 0%, rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.14), transparent 24%),
          radial-gradient(circle at 88% 10%, rgba(248, 113, 113, 0.08), transparent 18%),
          radial-gradient(circle at 50% 100%, rgba(129, 140, 248, 0.06), transparent 30%),
          linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg) 0%, var(--bg-2) 54%, var(--bg-3) 100%);
        overflow-x: hidden;
      }

      body::before {
        content: "";
        position: fixed;
        inset: 0;
        pointer-events: none;
        background:
          linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.014) 1px, transparent 1px),
          linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.012) 1px, transparent 1px);
        background-size: 36px 36px;
        mask-image: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18), transparent 32%, transparent 68%, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12));
        opacity: 0.22;
      }

      a {
        color: inherit;
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      img {
        display: block;
        max-width: 100%;
      }

      .page {
        width: min(var(--max), calc(100% - 2rem));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2rem 0 5rem;
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
      }

      .back-link {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.55rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        margin-bottom: 1.8rem;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        transition: color 220ms ease, transform 220ms ease;
      }

      .back-link:hover {
        color: var(--text);
        transform: translateX(-2px);
      }

      .hero {
        padding: 2rem 0 1.35rem;
        position: relative;
      }

      .hero::after {
        content: "";
        position: absolute;
        inset: -3rem -2rem auto auto;
        width: 340px;
        height: 340px;
        background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.12), transparent 68%);
        filter: blur(12px);
        pointer-events: none;
      }

      .eyebrow {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.45rem;
        padding: 0.42rem 0.8rem;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.22);
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.11), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03));
        color: var(--accent-cyan);
        font-size: 0.84rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.05rem;
        box-shadow: 0 8px 28px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18);
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: clamp(2.45rem, 4.8vw, 4.4rem);
        line-height: 1.02;
        letter-spacing: -0.04em;
        margin: 0 0 1rem;
        max-width: 980px;
      }

      .subtitle {
        max-width: 880px;
        font-size: 1.12rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        margin: 0 0 1.45rem;
      }

      .hero-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1.02fr 0.98fr;
        gap: 1.2rem;
        align-items: start;
      }

      .hero-copy {
        max-width: 820px;
      }

      .hero-copy p {
        margin: 0 0 0.9rem;
        font-size: 1.04rem;
        color: var(--soft);
      }

      .hero-outcome {
        margin-top: 1.15rem;
        max-width: 920px;
        padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
        border-radius: 18px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.24);
        background:
          linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.11), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03)),
          radial-gradient(circle at 0% 0%, rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.08), transparent 40%);
        color: #e7f4ff;
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
      }

      .hero-visual {
        overflow: hidden;
        padding: 0;
        border-radius: 24px;
        background:
          linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02)),
          radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.08), transparent 42%);
        border: 1px solid rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.18);
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
      }

      .hero-visual img {
        width: 100%;
        aspect-ratio: 16 / 10;
        object-fit: cover;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
      }

      .hero-visual-copy {
        padding: 1rem 1rem 1.05rem;
      }

      .hero-visual-copy strong {
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
        font-size: 1rem;
      }

      .hero-visual-copy p {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.94rem;
      }

      .metrics-label {
        margin-top: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
        font-size: 0.86rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--muted);
      }

      .metric-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem;
      }

      .metric {
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.025));
        border: 1px solid rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.17);
        border-radius: 20px;
        padding: 1.05rem 1rem 1.15rem;
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
        transition:
          transform 320ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          border-color 320ms ease,
          box-shadow 320ms ease,
          background 320ms ease;
      }

      .metric::before {
        content: "";
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0 auto auto 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        background: radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.1), transparent 55%);
        opacity: 0.8;
        pointer-events: none;
      }

      .metric:hover,
      .panel:hover,
      .proof-shot:hover,
      .image-panel:hover,
      .final-cta-panel:hover {
        transform: translateY(-6px);
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-lift);
      }

      .metric-bar {
        width: 54px;
        height: 3px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--accent-cyan), var(--accent-blue));
        margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
      }

      .metric-label {
        font-size: 0.92rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
      }

      .metric-value {
        font-size: 2rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      }

      .section {
        position: relative;
        padding-top: 4.4rem;
      }

      .section::before {
        content: "";
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0 0 auto 0;
        height: 1px;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.28), transparent);
        opacity: 0.55;
      }

      .section h2 {
        font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 3vw, 2.8rem);
        line-height: 1.08;
        letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        margin: 0 0 1rem;
      }

      .section-intro {
        max-width: 920px;
        color: var(--muted);
        margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
        font-size: 1.03rem;
      }

      .split {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1.15fr 0.85fr;
        gap: 1.2rem;
      }

      .panel {
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
        background:
          linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.028)),
          radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.08), transparent 48%),
          radial-gradient(circle at bottom right, rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.04), transparent 42%);
        border: 1px solid rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.18);
        border-radius: 22px;
        padding: 1.45rem;
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
        transition:
          transform 360ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          border-color 320ms ease,
          box-shadow 320ms ease;
      }

      .panel-strong {
        border-color: rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.28);
      }

      .panel h3 {
        margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        line-height: 1.25;
      }

      .panel p {
        margin: 0 0 1rem;
        color: var(--soft);
      }

      .panel p:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
      }

      .lead-strong {
        font-size: 1.08rem;
      }

      .list {
        margin: 0.1rem 0 0;
        padding-left: 1.15rem;
      }

      .list li {
        margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
        color: var(--soft);
      }

      .layer-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem;
        margin-top: 1.2rem;
      }

      .layer-card {
        padding: 1rem;
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.032), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.018));
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
        border-radius: 16px;
        transition:
          transform 300ms ease,
          border-color 300ms ease,
          background 300ms ease;
      }

      .layer-card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-4px);
        border-color: rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.2);
      }

      .layer-card h4 {
        margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
        font-size: 1rem;
      }

      .layer-card p {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.95rem;
      }

      .proof-image-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 1rem;
        margin-top: 1.35rem;
      }

      .image-panel,
      .proof-shot {
        overflow: hidden;
        border-radius: 22px;
        background:
          linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.022)),
          radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.06), transparent 42%);
        border: 1px solid rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.15);
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
        transition:
          transform 360ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          border-color 320ms ease,
          box-shadow 320ms ease;
      }

      .image-panel img,
      .proof-shot img {
        width: 100%;
        object-fit: cover;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
      }

      .image-panel img {
        aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
      }

      .proof-shot img {
        aspect-ratio: 16 / 10;
      }

      .image-copy,
      .proof-copy {
        padding: 1rem 1rem 1.05rem;
      }

      .image-copy strong,
      .proof-copy h3 {
        display: block;
        margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
        font-size: 1rem;
      }

      .image-copy p,
      .proof-copy p {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.94rem;
      }

      .callout {
        margin-top: 1.2rem;
        padding: 1.15rem 1.2rem;
        border-radius: 20px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.22);
        background:
          linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.11), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03)),
          radial-gradient(circle at left center, rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.08), transparent 42%);
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
      }

      .callout strong {
        color: #ffffff;
      }

      .final-signal-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem;
        margin-top: 1.2rem;
      }

      .signal-card {
        padding: 1rem 1rem 1.05rem;
        border-radius: 18px;
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02));
        border: 1px solid rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.16);
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
      }

      .signal-card p {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--soft);
      }

      .final-cta-section {
        padding-top: 3.4rem;
      }

      .final-cta-panel {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 1.5rem;
        padding: 1.5rem 1.6rem;
        border-radius: 24px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.2);
        background:
          linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.022)),
          radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.08), transparent 42%),
          radial-gradient(circle at bottom right, rgba(129, 140, 248, 0.06), transparent 38%);
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
        transition:
          transform 360ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          box-shadow 320ms ease;
      }

      .final-cta-copy {
        max-width: 760px;
      }

      .final-cta-kicker {
        margin: 0 0 0.55rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        font-size: 0.76rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--accent-cyan);
      }

      .final-cta-copy h2 {
        margin: 0 0 0.65rem;
        font-size: clamp(1.45rem, 2.3vw, 2rem);
        line-height: 1.1;
        letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      }

      .final-cta-copy p {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--muted);
      }

      .final-cta-actions {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 0.85rem;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: flex-end;
      }

      .final-button {
        min-height: 48px;
        padding: 0 1.15rem;
        border-radius: 999px;
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        font-weight: 700;
        transition:
          transform 220ms ease,
          border-color 220ms ease,
          background 220ms ease,
          box-shadow 220ms ease;
      }

      .final-button:hover {
        transform: translateY(-2px);
      }

      .final-button-primary {
        color: #07101f;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--accent-cyan), var(--accent-blue));
        box-shadow: 0 12px 28px rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.2);
      }

      .final-button-primary:hover {
        box-shadow: 0 16px 32px rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.26);
      }

      .final-button-secondary {
        color: var(--text);
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.14);
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
      }

      .final-button-secondary:hover {
        border-color: rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.24);
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.07);
      }

      .footer-space {
        height: 0.75rem;
      }

      .reveal {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(28px);
        transition:
          opacity 700ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          transform 700ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
        transition-delay: var(--delay, 0ms);
        will-change: opacity, transform;
      }

      .reveal.is-visible {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateY(0);
      }

      .reveal-left {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateX(-26px);
        transition:
          opacity 720ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          transform 720ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
        transition-delay: var(--delay, 0ms);
      }

      .reveal-left.is-visible {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateX(0);
      }

      .reveal-right {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateX(26px);
        transition:
          opacity 720ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          transform 720ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
        transition-delay: var(--delay, 0ms);
      }

      .reveal-right.is-visible {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateX(0);
      }

      @media (max-width: 980px) {
        .hero-grid,
        .metric-grid,
        .split,
        .layer-grid,
        .proof-image-grid,
        .final-signal-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .page {
          width: min(var(--max), calc(100% - 1.15rem));
        }

        .hero {
          padding-top: 1.2rem;
        }

        h1 {
          font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 10vw, 3.4rem);
        }

        .final-cta-panel {
          flex-direction: column;
          align-items: flex-start;
        }

        .final-cta-actions {
          justify-content: flex-start;
        }
      }

      @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
        html {
          scroll-behavior: auto;
        }

        *,
        *::before,
        *::after {
          animation: none !important;
          transition: none !important;
        }

        .reveal,
        .reveal-left,
        .reveal-right {
          opacity: 1 !important;
          transform: none !important;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <main class="page">
      <a href="/" class="back-link reveal" style="--delay: 0ms;">← Back to portfolio</a>

      <section class="hero">
        <div class="eyebrow reveal" style="--delay: 40ms;">AI Reliability • LLMOps • Governance</div>
        <h1 class="reveal" style="--delay: 80ms;">{pageTitle}</h1>
        <p class="subtitle reveal" style="--delay: 140ms;">{pageDescription}</p>

        <div class="hero-grid">
          <div class="hero-copy">
            <p class="reveal" style="--delay: 200ms;">
              I built this project around a harder question than “can the assistant answer claims questions?” The real question was whether a Swiss insurer could trust that assistant enough to release it into controlled production use.
            </p>
            <p class="reveal" style="--delay: 260ms;">
              That meant the project had to go beyond a useful interface or a decent retrieval flow. It needed governed release behavior, benchmark discipline, escalation-sensitive evaluation, live telemetry, incident logic, review workflows, and containment recommendations if live behavior later became unsafe.
            </p>

            <div class="hero-outcome reveal" style="--delay: 320ms;">
              The result is a full trust-loop case: a governed claims assistant, a release gate that caught a real boundary-handling bug, and a packaged live monitoring layer that can detect unsafe post-release behavior, open review workflows, and recommend rollback.
            </div>
          </div>

          <figure class="hero-visual reveal-right" style="--delay: 240ms;">
            <img
              src={imageAssets.heroLoop}
              alt="Trust loop visual for the Claims AI Reliability Platform showing governed assistant, release gate, monitoring, incidents, review, and rollback"
            />
            <figcaption class="hero-visual-copy">
              <strong>The trust loop this project proves</strong>
              <p>
                Release discipline before deployment, and containment logic after deployment.
              </p>
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>

        <div class="metrics-label reveal" style="--delay: 380ms;">Proof of project weight</div>

        <div class="metric-grid">
          {heroMetrics.map((metric, index) => (
            <div class="metric reveal" style={`--delay: ${420 + index * 70}ms;`}>
              <div class="metric-bar"></div>
              <div class="metric-label">{metric.label}</div>
              <div class="metric-value">{metric.value}</div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="reveal">Why a normal prototype was not enough</h2>
